<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Extends Support for Declaration of Independent  Palestine State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh extended her support
for declaration of an independent Palestine state, Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina told visiting Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
"We are always with the Palestinian people. Bangladesh attaches
high importance to the development of the existing friendly
relations with Palestine," Hasina said during the official talks
with Arafat.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader told Hasina that he had mastered support
from 120 countries including the Organization of the Islamic
Conference and the Arab League in his efforts for the declaration
of an independent Palestine state.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said three permanent members of the United Nations
Security Council, China, Russia and France, also lent their
support to the declaration.
</P>
<P>
"Now I am waiting for support from the United States and the
United Kingdom," he said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat came here on a working visit from Tokyo to drum up
Bangladesh's support for the declaration of an independent
Palestine state. Later, he left here for New Delhi to continue
his South Asian tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
