<HEADLINE> Exiled Ex-President of Cote d'Ivoire to Return Home for Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS,August 18(Xinhua)-- Former President of Cote d'Ivoire
Henri Konan Bedie, living now in exile here, is going home on
September 3 to participate in his country's presidential election
in October,the local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Bedie, who was overthrown in a military coup d'etat late last
December, made the decision although his security will not be
guaranteed, Agence France-Presse quoted an official of his party
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bedie has been chosen by the French and European sections of
his Democratic Party of Cote d'Ivoire (PDCI) as the presidential
candidate and is expected to be formally nominated at a party
meeting in Yamoussoukro, Cote d'Ivoire on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
His return was opposed by General Robert Guei, leader of the
coup d'etat and the current junta in Abidjan.
</P>
<P>
A total of 19 persons, including Guei, have so far registered
for the October presidential election in Cote d'Ivoire, which is
the final step to restore civilian rule in the western African
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
