<HEADLINE> Ukrainian President Deplores Tragedy in Barents Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to reports of the Interfax-Ukraine news agency,
Kuchma told reporters in Foros, Crimea, that "there were a lot of
Ukrainians on this submarine". "I know that many submariners, who
used to serve in the Black Sea Fleet, have moved to Russia", he
added.
</P>
<P>
"The whole world, not only Ukraine, is watching with pain the
situation in the Barents Sea", the president noted.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said that in this situation his country "can help Russia
only with its sympathy", because Ukraine has no means to help
Russia. "May the people, trapped on the submarine, have a positive
outcome of this situation", he added. 
</P>
