<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian chief negotiator Saeb Erekat said on
Saturday that U.S. Middle East envoy Dennis Ross did not carry any
fresh proposals from the U.S. Administration to end the stalemate
in the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Erekat, who met Ross at an undisclosed place in Jerusalem on
Friday, told reporters that a new summit, following the failed Camp
David peace summit on July 11-25, needed intensive preparations,
estimations and clarifications on the Israeli position.(Palestine-
US Envoy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- A Russian plane arrived at the newly opened Saddam
International Airport in the capital Baghdad on Saturday on a "
humanitarian mission" to sanctions-stricken Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, carrying humanitarian supplies, mainly baby food,
medicine and medical equipment, landed at the airport at 18:10
local time (1410 GMT).
</P>
<P>
This was the first direct flight from Moscow since the end of
the Gulf War in 1991. Russian Deputy Minister of Civil Defense and
Emergency Situations Ruslan Tsalikov, at the head of a 25-member
delegation, told reporters that his country did not ask for
permission for the flight from the United Nations Sanctions
Committee for the trip. (Iraq-Russia-Plane)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa conferred with
visiting U.S. Middle East envoy Dennis Ross on the Mideast peace
process Saturday in the Mediterranean port city of Alexandria.
</P>
<P>
The two officials discussed prospects of giving a boost to the
negotiations between the Palestinians and Israelis, and tried to
seek means of overcoming a number of impediments in the peace
process, a statement issued by Egypt's Foreign Ministry said.
(Egypt-US-Mideast Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- An Iraqi military spokesman said on Saturday that an
American plane has been shut down in southern Iraq by its anti-air
defenses, the official Iraqi News Agency (INA)reported.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Yassin Jasim, major general of the Iraqi
Air Defense Command, said that the plane was shut down on July 26
and crashed in the Saudi desert. (Iraq-US-Plane)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian side totally opposes the idea of
internationalizing the holy sites in Jerusalem, said Secretary
General of the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) Abu Mazen.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held in the West Bank city of Ramallah,
Abu Mazen, also known as Mahmoud Abbas, denied reports that Egypt
had put forward new initiatives regarding the future of Jerusalem
during his recent visit to Cairo. (Palestine-Jerusalem) 
</P>
