<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bogota Recovers Its Original Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's capital, Santa Fe de
Bogota, has recovered its original name, Bogota, by cutting off
Santa Fe as part of the city's name.
</P>
<P>
President Andres Pastrana approved Friday Legislative Act No. 1.
by which the Congress of the Republic approved the constitutional
reform that leaves the name of the city as simply Bogota.
</P>
<P>
Legislative Act No.1 signed by President Pastrana and Interior
Minister Humberto De la Calle Lombana, establishes that "Bogota,
capital of the Republic and of the department of Cundinamarca,
center of the country, is organized as the Capital District."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
