<HEADLINE> British Rescuers Arrive in Kursk Accident Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 19 (Xinhua) -- British rescuers arrived Saturday
evening in the area where a Russian nuclear submarine with 118
crew went down a week ago.
</P>
<P>
They arrived aboard the Norwegian ship Normand Pioneer, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Britain's LR-5 mini-submarine will take British and Russian
rescuers to the bottom of the Barents Sea where the cripple Kursk
is lying.
</P>
<P>
