<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Chronology of Beijing's Laoshan Tomb Excavation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The excavation of the 2,000-year-
old Laoshan Tomb, located 10 kilometers west of downtown Beijing,
has been going on for about eight months.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, local residents spotted some new
hillocks in Laoshan. On December 24, several people, suspected of
stealing from the tomb, were arrested by local police. Two days
later, archeologists from Beijing Bureau of Cultural Heritage
confirmed that an ancient tomb exists in the area.
</P>
<P>
Archeological workers began to excavate the tomb on January 17
year, with ratification from the State Bureau of Cultural Heritage.
A preliminary estimate was that the tomb belonged to a king from
the Western Han Dynasty (206 B.C.- 24 A.D.).
</P>
<P>
In early April, the shape of the outer coffin appeared after
the earth in the tomb was cleared out. "Ticou," the structure of
lots of piled-up wooden poles, used only by family members of the
king to protect coffins, were also discovered in the tomb chamber.
</P>
<P>
The outer coffin, all parts of the "Ticou" and the outer
cloister of the tomb had all been excavated by the end of April.
Burial objects of pottery and pieces of lacquerware were also
found.
</P>
<P>
From May 2, workers began to build a 36-meter-long canopy over
the site to protect it from the weather.
</P>
<P>
After the construction was completed at the end of July,
workers started to excavate the inside parts of the tomb chamber.
More lacquerware, a pottery tripod caldron and some well-preserved
tiles were unearthed.
</P>
<P>
The excavation has come to a crucial stage at present. All
preliminary preparations have been finished and archeologists now
are ready to open the coffin.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday morning, the China Central Television, the largest TV
station in the country, will broadcast live for the first time
how archeologists excavate the front chamber of the Laoshan Tomb.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000819.0034 </DOCNO>
