<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Launches Development Programs to Reconstruct CHT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Red Crescent Society (
BDRCS) Saturday formally launched a package of development
programs to reconstruct the insurgency-battered Chittagong Hill
Tracts (CHT) region in the southeast part of the country, the
official Bangladesh News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the BDRCS, the programs include primary health
services, especially health services to mothers and children,
creation of new sources of safe drinking water, creation of
awareness on sanitation and drainage system, usage of hygienic
latrines, generation of self-employment of women, education and
income generation activities.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the development efforts of the BDRCS, Minister for
Chittagong Hill Tracts Affairs Kaiparanjan Chakma urged the
society to go ahead with development activities as people of CHT
could not witness the touch of development in the past 20 to 25
years due to political unrest.
</P>
<P>
"Peace and cooperation is the precondition of development," he
observed.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the BDRCS to establish agro-based industries in
the region to bring about a positive change in the socio-economic
condition of the people in this region.
</P>
<P>
The CHT affairs minister finally expressed the hope that
development activities in the region would be implemented in full
swing as the development partners from abroad are found
spontaneous in investment in CHT region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
