<HEADLINE> E-Post Services Introduced in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Postal Department
entered the age of Internet Saturday by formally introducing "e-
post(electronic post)", first of its kind in the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation countries.
</P>
<P>
The majority of people who have no computer of e-mail
connection, can send and receive e-mails through the e-post
service, Post and Telecommunications Secretary Nazmul Ahsan
Chowdhury said while inaugurating the e-post service.
</P>
<P>
Initially e-mails could be sent and received only in Dhaka, and
soon the e-post service would be extended to other places across
the country in phases.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the function, the secretary said postal department
as a service-oriented organization has introduced e-post in the
new millenium to keep abreast of the technological innovation.
</P>
<P>
It is only the first step, and more work should be done to
facilitate the common people with the modern technological devices,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh Postal Department has also introduced fastest
Express Parcel Service from August 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
