<HEADLINE> Kenya's Population Growth High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's population growth is too
high that it poses a major challenge to the country's development
objectives, the official newspaper Kenya Times quoted a senior
official as saying Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The country's population increased by 34 percent between 1989
and 1999, which is much higher considering the limited resources
of the east African country, Kenyan Minister for Planning and
National Development Gideon Ndambuki said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ndambuki attributed the high population growth to high
fertility resulting from unwanted pregnancies and desire to have
large families.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government had taken measures to reduce
population growth rate which included a wide range of effective
family planning services across the country.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's population amounted to 28.7 million, according to the
provisional results of last year's census.
</P>
</TEXT>
