<DOCNO> XIE20000819.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Nature Reserve of Three-River Headwaters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sanjiangyuan nature reserve
set up today in where China's three major rivers originate is the
largest and highest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The nature reserve covers an area of 362,000 square kilometers
and is located at an average altitude of 4,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
The area in southern Qinghai Province, northwest China, is the
source of the Yangtze, Yellow and Lancang rivers, contributing 25,
50 and 15 percent of the water to the three rivers.
</P>
<P>
There are over 70 species of rare wildlife including Tibetan
antelope and wild donkey in this reserve.
</P>
<P>
The nature reserve also covers 16 counties with a total
population of 557,200 people, mostly Tibetans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
