<HEADLINE> China's Longest Expressway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A 652-kilometer expressway, the
longest in China connecting Guilin, a major scenic city and Beihai,
a seaside resort in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, opens to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
Now it takes only five or six hours to travel from Guilin to
Beihai.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the expressway began in October, 1993. It costs
more than 10.5 billion yuan (about 126.5 million U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
Guangxi now ranks the fifth in the total length of the
expressway in China. 
</P>
