<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Celebrates Judicial Police Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Day of Judicial Police of the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) was celebrated here
Saturday and some outstanding individuals and judicial police
groups were commended.
</P>
<P>
Cheong Kuok Va, secretary for security of the Macao SAR
government, noted that the judicial police have cracked many big
cases and contributed a lot to safeguarding public security since
the founding of the SAR in last December.
</P>
<P>
"This year, the leadership of the judicial police has conducted
a series of reforms which help raise the efficiency of criminal
investigation and make the work of judicial police more
transparent," he said.
</P>
<P>
With more contacts with the outside world, the judicial police
may face ever greater challenges in combating trans-border crimes,
Cheong said, adding that local police authorities have established
good ties with counterpart departments of the state and
neighboring Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
"But one point is certain, all difficulties will be overcome
with the concerted efforts of all members of the judicial police,
with the common goal of protecting public security, together with
the cooperation of other police forces," he said.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 19 individuals and five police groups were commended.
Chief Executive of the Macao SAR Edmund Ho Hau Wah attended the
celebration and awarded prizes to part of the outstanding
individuals. 
</P>
