<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Exploit New Natural Gas Resource </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The government of Pakistan has
already approved a 20-billion-Rupee (about 46 million U.S. dollars)
project to capitalize on new discoveries of natural gas in
Southern Pakistan, officials of the Ministry of Petroleum and
Natural Resources said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The project is aimed at making full use of the new discoveries
in the South that will add approximately 950 million cubic feet
per day of gas to the existing system," said Jahangir Basher, the
spokesman of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
He said that the supply of additional gas under the project
will allow a larger number of domestic and industrial users to use
the natural resource.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, the supply of additional gas will enable the power
generation units using oil as fuel to switch over to the use of
natural gas, thus saving the country's hefty oil import bills.
</P>
</TEXT>
