half-day visit to Nepal on August 25. (Japan-Mori-Departure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- The Yugoslav government strongly condemned Friday
the bomb attack by unidentified attackers on a building in central
Pristina as perpetrating ethnic cleansing and attempting to
destroy all signs of the Yugoslav presence in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, occurring at 9:30 a.m. (0730 GMT) when more than
20 people were working in the building, dilapidated offices and
caused injuries and great economic damage. The building houses
offices of the Yugoslav Committee for Cooperation with the U.N.
Mission in Kosovo. In a statement, the government said the
terrorist act came only four days after the NATO-led peacekeeping
force in Kosovo (KFOR) forcefully occupied a Serb lead refinery. (
Yugoslavia-Condemnation)
</P>
