<HEADLINE> Agassi Reaches Semifinals at Classic Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- American Andre Agassi held
off a tough quarterfinal challenge from 17-year-old Andy Roddick
to make the semifinals of the men's Classic tournament Friday.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, seeking his sixth here title in 11 years, beat the hard-
serving Australian Open junior champion 6-4, 6-4, extending his
Washington win streak to 13 matches without losing a set.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Alex Corretja of Spain had more trouble reaching
the semifinals as he survived a tie breaker and a second set loss
to beat Wayne Arthurs of Australia 7-6 (7-5), 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the other quarterfinal match, third-seeded Nicolas Kiefer of
Germany climbed back after losing the first set to eliminate fifth-
seeded American Jan-Michael Gambill 4-6, 6-4, 6-2. He plays
Corretja in the other semifinal match. 
</P>
