<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Helicopter Co-operation Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Harbin Aircraft Industry
Group Corp on Friday produced its 200th fuselage, for the five-
seater EC120 helicopter -- a joint program between China, France
and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The EC120 helicopter program started in 1993 and it was the
first time China had shared investment and risks with a foreign
partner in helicopter production, Zhang Yanzhong, general manager
of China Aviation Industry Corp II, mother of the Harbin company,
was quoted as saying by today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
China holds a 24-percent share in the company while France-
based Eurocopter owns 61 percent and Singapore-based Technologies
Aerospace holds the remaining 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The single-engine helicopter is designed to meet both military
and civilian requirements, including search-and-rescue and
evacuation operation, intelligence uses and other applications.
</P>
<P>
By now, the Harbin company had received 256 orders for EC120
helicopter by the end of June this year, of which 110 were
delivered.  
</P>
</TEXT>
