<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sciences to Help Development of Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Science
and Technology has designed a series of science-based programs to
help accelerate the development of China's backward western
regions.
</P>
<P>
The programs include such measures as experiments in water-
saving agriculture and afforestation to stop the expansion of
deserts in the west and administrative and specialized skills for
county officials; spread of advanced farming techniques and
introduction of high-tech zones and university-based scientific
parks.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the program are directing science and
technology institutions in Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin to
support Yunnan and Sichuan provinces and Xinjiang and Inner
Mongolia and helping the west select science projects for the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also enhance co-operation with Europe for the
development of agriculture, fisheries and forestry, build Sino-
Russian agricultural projects in China's dry and semi-dry west,
and popularise the use of poverty-relief, farm produce processing
and water-saving agriculture programs offered by the World Bank
and other international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Since the central government launched its western development
campaign early this year, the ministry has spent more than 270
million yuan (32.5 million U.S. dollars) on development in western
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
