<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News in China This Week (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of diplomatic news
released by Xinhua on August 13-18:
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Meets U.S. Congressman
</P>
<P>
The policy of "peaceful reunification and one country, two
systems" remains unchanged, however, the one-China principle is
the prerequisite and basis for resuming dialog and negotiations
between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits, Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said in a meeting with Bill Archer, member of the U.S.
House of Representatives and chairman of the House Ways and Means
Committee last Monday.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, also met him the same day.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Meets Arafat
</P>
<P>
President Jiang told visiting Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat last Monday that China believes the Palestinian authorities
led by Arafat will choose an "appropriate time" to declare
statehood.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the Palestinian National Authority led by
Arafat will think it over and declare statehood at an appropriate
time to achieve the best possible results," Jiang was quoted by a
spokesman of the Foreign Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived in Beijing Monday morning for a working visit.
He left here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Grants Interview to CBS Anchor
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin gave an interview to a Columbia
Broadcasting System (CBS) anchor Tuesday at the seaside resort of
Beidaihe, 300 kilometers east of Beijing, and answered his
questions on Sino-U.S. relations and China's domestic matters. (
more)
