<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Raps Bomb Attack on Kosovo Office Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav government
strongly condemned Friday the bomb attack by unidentified
attackers on a building in central Pristina as perpetrating
ethnic cleansing and attempting to destroy all signs of the
Yugoslav presence in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, occurring at 9:30 a.m. (0730 GMT) when more than
20 people were working in the building, dilapidated offices and
caused injuries and great economic damage. The building houses
offices of the Yugoslav Committee for Cooperation with the U.N.
Mission in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the government said the terrorist act came only
four days after the NATO-led peacekeeping force in Kosovo (KFOR)
forcefully occupied a Serb lead refinery.
</P>
<P>
It was another encroachment upon Yugoslavia's sovereignty and
territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
The two incidents indicated that the ethnic Albanian terrorists,
cooperating with forces under the disguise of the United Nations,
started another round of terrorist intimidation and ethnic
cleansing against peaceful civilians, public establishments and
state workers, the statement noted.
</P>
<P>
It said that pressed by the U.S. government, the U.N. special
mission has become an accomplice of Albanian separatists and
instrument to carry out ethnic cleansing and to destabilize the
region.
</P>
<P>
Since the U.N. mission and NATO-led peacekeepers entered Kosovo
last June following the end of NATO's 78-day bombing on Yugoslavia,
a total of 1,038 persons were killed, 960 kidnapped and 360,000
non-Albanian residents forced to flee their homes.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged an end to such a mission in order to defend
the dignity of the U.N., maintain peace and stability in the
region, and ensure a political settlement to the Kosovo issue.
</P>
</TEXT>
