the 2000-2001 period in April. The country hopes to achieve the
integration, especially the Latin American integration, during its
presidency term.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Chavez underscored the necessity to draft a
working agenda to solve the issue. He also stressed the importance
of the restart of the bloc to bloc negotiations for the
integration of the Andean Community, made up of Bolivia, Colombia,
Ecuador, Peru, Venezuela, and the Southern Common Market (Mercosur)
formed by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Integration System consists of 60 representatives of
political, juridical and social organizations. 
