<HEADLINE> Honduras Records Four Cases of New Type of Dengue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Honduras Health Ministry
has confirmed four cases of a new variety of hemorrhage dengue,
raising the number to eight recorded this year, a ministry
official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Two of the four cases were registered in Tegucigalpa, and the
other two in the eastern department of Olancho, said Epidemiology
Department chief Marco Antonio Pinel.
</P>
<P>
None of the eight persons with the fatal disease has died, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Pinel said some 3,000 cases of classic dengue have been
registered this year, 6,000 less than in 1999.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that on August 28, the government will launch
a nationwide campaign to eradicate water pools, where the "Aedes
Aegypti" mosquito transmitting the dengue breeds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
