<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Drug Trafficker Extradited to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Colombian citizen Alberto
Orlandez Gamboa, known as "The Snail," was extradited Friday to
the United States for drug trafficking, President Pastrana
announced during his visit to Medellin.
</P>
<P>
Charged as the head of the Atlantic Coast drug trafficking
cartel, Orlandez was arrested in August, 1999, at the request of a
U.S. judge, who requested the extradition.
</P>
<P>
Orlandez, 44, is the third Colombian citizen extradited to the
United States in nine years.
</P>
<P>
A 1997 Constitutional revision reestablished the extradition of
Colombian citizens when requested by U.S. judges.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana said that the government rejected the recourses filed
by Orlandez, whose extradition has been approved by the Supreme
Court of Justice.
</P>
<P>
Drug dealers threatened that they will begin assassination
attacks at Colombian leaders and Supreme Court judges until the
government reverses its decision to extradite Orlandez, one of the
52 suspected drug traffickers awaiting trail in U.S. courts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
