<HEADLINE> Hingis and Serena Endter Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis
and reigning US Open champion Serena Williams beat their rivals
respectively Friday to enter the semi-finals of the WTA Canadian
Open in Montreal, Canada.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Hingis knocked out French eighth seed Sandrine Testud
6-4, 4-6, 6-3 while Williams whipped fellow American Amy Frazier 6-
0, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Swiss teen Hingis, ensured of being the top-ranked woman when
next week's US Open seeds are made, advanced to a semi-final
against third seed Conchita Martinez of Spain, who beat Luxembourg
's Anne Kremer 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Williams faces the winner of a late match between Bulgaria's
Magdalena Maleeva and seventh seed Arantxa Sachez-Vicario of Spain.
</P>
