<HEADLINE> Indonesia Picks up Archer Hamdiah For Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Archery
Association has decided to send Hamdiah to compete in the
individual event of the Olympic Games in Sydney next month.
</P>
<P>
The Olympics executive training deputy Imron Z. Syarifuddin
said Hamdiah outclassed teammates Nurfitriyana Lantang Saiman and
Lusia Elizabeth Sampow in the championships in South Korea from
August 9 to 16.
</P>
<P>
"The overseas tryout in South Korea showed that Hamdiah looked
better than Nurfitriyana and Lusia," he was quoted by the Jakarta
Post Saturday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Archery Association's Secretary General Udi
Harsono said there was no hope for the team events.
</P>
<P>
"We don't expect any special invitation from the International
Olympics Committee. It's getting more difficult now to get a berth
forour team event," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hamdiah qualified for the Olympics after she managed to reach
the quarterfinals of the 40th World Archery Tournament in Riom,
France,last year. In the quarterfinals, however, she bowed out to
South Korea's Lee Kyung-eun. 
</P>
</TEXT>
