<HEADLINE> Paraguayan Defense Minister Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Paraguayan President Luis
Gonzalez Macchi announced that Defense Minister Nelson Argana
resigned Friday.
</P>
<P>
Argana, brother of Felix Argana, the ruling Colorado Party
candidate in last Sunday's vice presidential elections, will be
replaced by the commander of the military forces, Rear Admiral
Ramon Ocampo Alfaro, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Asuncion said that the resignation
occurred when the final results of the elections were about to be
announced. The Higher Court of Electoral Justice resumed Thursday
to scrutinize the ballots that were interrupted on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Colorado Party candidate said Thursday that his family
members, who hold posts in the government, will withdraw if he is
confirmed to have defeated in the elections. 
</P>
