<HEADLINE> Mexico's President-elect Starts Visit to Belize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President-elect
Vicente Fox arrived Friday in Belize for a four-hour visit, during
which he will meet Prime Minister Said Musa and businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Before meeting Fox in private, Musa said that Fox's visit will
help consolidate bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Musa said that the very fact that the Mexican president-elect
has chosen Belize for his first trip to a neighboring country is
of great significance for Belize as it provides the leaders of the
two countries a chance to meet and discuss commercial, economic,
cultural and education matters.
</P>
<P>
Fox was elected on July 2, ending 71 years of single-party rule
in Mexico. He will assume office on December 1. 
</P>
