<HEADLINE> Four Bombs Damage Bank Offices in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Four bombs were detonated
Saturday in the same number of bank offices in Bogota, Colombia,
allegedly by guerrilla members, and no victims reported, police
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The devices detonated in the Ganadero and Santander bank
offices in the south and the center of the city, as well as in two
automatic tellers in the La Calera and Soacha localities, on the
city's outskirts.
</P>
<P>
The detonations destroyed windows and facades of the banks,
which were simultaneously closed to the public, and this was the
cause for the absence of victims.
</P>
<P>
Police attributed the Saturday attacks to guerrilla urban
commandos, after the attack on Friday by members of the National
Liberation Army (ELN) to two bank offices in Cali.
</P>
<P>
The explosions occur 11 days before U.S. President Bill Clinton
's visit to Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas have stated their rejection to Clinton's visit
and to the United States' meddling in the internal affairs of
Colombia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
