<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright Saturday wound up her visit to Ecuador as part of a tour
of several South American countries.
</P>
<P>
Albright promised Ecuadoran officials for a social and economic
development program in the border of that country with Colombia,
as well as 15 million U.S. dollars for the attention of people
displaced by the Colombian internal armed conflict.
</P>
<P>
