The U.S. secretary of State visited Brazil, Argentina, Chile,
Bolivia and Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
She signed during her 20-hour visit to Ecuador an agreement for
the donation of U.S. food worth 26.3 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Albright described Ecuador as a "key country" for the
strengthening of democracy in the region and considered necessary
the improvement of the judicial system and a constructive
political opposition.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, she said her country supports the plans for a
reduction of part of the Ecuadoran foreign debt.  
