according to the National Provisional Charter adopted on July 6
this year.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are at least seven candidates for the speaker
post.
</P>
<P>
Of all the candidates, Cabdalla Deerow Isaaq is most likely to
be elected as parliament speaker, the first officially recognized
top legislator of Somalia since the country fell into turmoil in
1991.
</P>
<P>
Deerow, 50, is a prominent political and traditional leader of
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
He is from Digil and Mirifle clan, one of the major clans in
southwest Somalia. 
