<HEADLINE> Kaunda Children's Foundation Launched in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The long awaited Kenneth Kaunda
Children of Africa Foundation (KKF) has been officially launched
by its Executive Director Robet Penny in Zambia on behalf of
Kaunda who is currently out of the country, Sunday Mail newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
The practical launch will be done by Kenneth Kaunda, Zambian
former president and founder of the organization in the next few
weeks, said Penny at a press briefing here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We have so far registered our organization in six countries
mainly in the Southern Africa," Penny said, adding that the
intention of the foundation is not to compete with other
organizations but to create alliances with the already existing
ones and internationalize it to hold public awareness campaigns on
the devastation the HIV/AIDS scourge has caused in Africa.
</P>
<P>
"We will use Kaunda to get the conscience of the people who are
unaware of the devastating levels of HIV/AIDS in Africa. We are
going to break the silence which unfortunately has existed.
African countries have been pretty silent on the problems of HIV/
AIDS, so our mission is to break that silence," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the foundation is all about the children of Africa
who have fallen victims of the scourge after the deaths of their
parents and his organization was overwhelmed by the positive
response of the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
heads of states at the recent Windhoek summit in Namibia.
</P>
<P>
Some of the objectives of the foundation are to initiate
programs that will break the poverty/AIDS cycle through education,
skills training and job creation, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
