<HEADLINE> Chinese President Congratulates on Unveiling of Bethune Statue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
extends warm congratulations on the unveiling of the bronze statue
of Canadian Doctor Norman Bethune in a letter announced Saturday
at the unveiling ceremony in Dr. Bethune's hometown, Gravenhurst,
Ontario. The full text of the letter is as follows:
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion of the inauguration of the bronze statue of Dr.
Bethune, I wish to express, on behalf of the Chinese government
and people and in my own name, my warm congratulations to the
Memorial Hall of Bethune.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Bethune is an outstanding son of the Canadian people and a
great friend of the Chinese people. He came to China, making light
of traveling thousands of miles, to help the Chinese people in the
War of Resistance against Japanese aggression and sacrificed his
precious life for this cause. Though more than six decades have
passed, his name remains a household word in China. His spirit of
internationalism and his utter devotion to others without any
thought of self are still on everyone's lips around China. He has
become the symbol of the long-standing friendship between our two
peoples. Today, the seeds of Sino-Canadian friendship that he
personally sown have yielded rich fruits.
</P>
<P>
May the spirit of Dr. Bethune shine perpetually!
</P>
<P>
May Sino-Canadian friendship last forever!" 
</P>
</TEXT>
